	(text "Low Frequency IO Pins: \n= P0.02 P0.03 P0.09 P0.10 P0.28 P0.29 P0.30 P0.31\n= P1.01 P1.02 P1.03 P1.04 P1.05 P1.06 P1.07 P1.10 \n= P1.11 P1.12 P1.13 P1.14 P1.15\n\nStandard Frequency IO Pins:\n= P0.00 P0.01 P0.04 P0.05 P0.06 P0.07 P0.08 P0.11 \n= P0.12 P0.13 P0.14 P0.15 P0.16 P0.17 P0.18 P0.19\n= P0.20 P0.21 P0.22 P0.23 P0.24 P0.25 P0.26 P0.27\n= P1.00 P1.08 P1.09\n\nP0.18 is the nRESET Pin.\n\nBe careful with the pin assignments as not every\npin can handle a high speed signal"
